        "created_at": "2021-08-17T20:20:11.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"172836\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"172836\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Interesting article in Vinography by Alder Yarrow on the Savoie wines of Domaine Curtet:<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.vinography.com/2021/08/the-forest-dreams-of-the-savoie-vine-the-wines-of-domaine-curtet\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://www.vinography.com/2021/08/the-forest-dreams-of-the-savoie-vine-the-wines-of-domaine-curtet</a><br>\nwho sounds a bit like he farms by Fukuoka, or one step beyond that. He\u2019s working w/ an interesting selection<br>\nof Savoie varieties. He wants to eventually grow all the genetic relatives of Mondeuse. He rejects many of the<br>\ntenents of farming BioDynamic as contrived &amp; artificial. He\u2019s a \u201cnatural\u201d winemakers but rejects the idea of any<br>\nmousey character in his wines. <strong>That\u2019s a bit shocking</strong>.</p>\n<p>Anybody tried the Curtet wines?? And?? Production is only around 2500 cs. Don\u2019t know if they\u2019re imported into the US or not.</p>\n<p>Tom</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I\u2019m not sure I read it the same way as you.  He uses sulfites at bottling to prevent mouse taint.  I don\u2019t think avoiding mousiness is shocking, although perhaps using sulfites is.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Well, Jason\u2026 I was just being a bit sarcastic. As Bueker will tell you, I like to  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/f/f40faec63ca1018898a40805efbf9f0066a3d205.gif\" width=\"29\" height=\"36\" alt=\"[stirthepothal.gif]\" title=\"[stirthepothal.gif]\" class=\"animated\"> .<br>\nTom</p>",
