      {
        "id": 3218252,
        "name": "Steve Anderson",
        "username": "Steve_Anderson",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/steve_anderson/{size}/820_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-08-18T04:08:44.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Tom - thank you for posting, as I had not seen this and recently started penciling out a Savoie visit for next year.  Curtet was already on my short list of potential visits, but now will be one I certainly reach out to.  I\u2019ll seek out a white based on William\u2019s feedback but enjoyed the Pinot Noir quite a bit about a year ago.  Not Burgundy, but likely doesn\u2019t aspire to be.  I recall a nice minerality, and good fruit, although a touch on the tart/slightly under ripe side.  IT was good enough that I would purchase again if I came across it.</p>\n<p>You are most likely to find it in shops that cater to \u201cNatural\u201d wine.  Vino Carta in San Diego has carried it, but typically in small numbers, and not seeing any in their current inventory.  I do see options in Wine Searcher.</p>",
